<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="65" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,562,2028]" pageId="16" pageNumber="65">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,321,598,623]" pageId="16" pageNumber="65">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
A 
<taxonomicName box="[355,483,598,623]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechisibus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[355,483,598,623]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="65">Trechisibus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species 
<quantity box="[578,678,599,623]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.42" pageId="16" pageNumber="65" unit="mm" value="3.42">3.42 mm</quantity>
long, dark brown and shiny; legs, antennae, mouth parts and lateral border of elytra reddish brown. Hind angles of pronotum acute and protruding backwards and outwards. Elytra short oval, obovate, widest behind middle, moderately depressed on disc, with 2 discal setigerous punctures (in addition to the preapical pore) on the 3rd stria, the first at about 1/5 from base and the second just behind middle. 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechisibus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevis" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="65">T. brevis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[228,295,742,767]" pageId="16" pageNumber="65">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[228,295,742,767]" pageId="16" pageNumber="65" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
is distinguished from all other 
<taxonomicName box="[666,794,742,767]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Trechisibus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="65" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[666,794,742,767]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="65">Trechisibus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species distributed in Patagonia by the body short and obovate (
<figureCitation box="[254,335,778,803]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1453,1475]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,418,1423]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1437,411,1432]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Trechisibus brevis n. sp. HT: habitus (a); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view (b); median lobe of aedeagus in dorsal view (c)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166628/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="65">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
a) and by the peculiar morphology of the median lobe of aedeagus, provided with a distinct ventral swelling in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[428,511,813,838]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1453,1475]" captionTargetBox="[162,1421,418,1423]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[150,1437,411,1432]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Trechisibus brevis n. sp. HT: habitus (a); median lobe of aedeagus in lateral view (b); median lobe of aedeagus in dorsal view (c)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/166628/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="65">Fig. 10</figureCitation>
b).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
